msgid "No."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0004"
msgid "Let me check..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0005"
msgid "Never mind."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0006"
msgid "Some...thing?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0010"
msgid "I have one now!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0011"
msgid "That's some request..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0012"
msgid "That's fair. I have one."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0013"
msgid "Never mind."
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk_00"
msgid ""
"Ho ho ho...<1.pa> At last!<2.pa> Free of that tiny\n"
"bud after so long! If my arms were\n"
"corporeal, they'd have cramped for sure!\n"
"And you're the one who set me free, are\n"
"you not?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (20f)
#. 2: pause (20f)
msgctxt "talk_00_01"
msgid ""
"It's you again... <1.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Why have you sought me out? Surely\n"
"no ill has befallen your beloved, faithful\n"
"steeds... <2.pa>Let me see..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (red)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: set_colour (red)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk_00_1"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My name is <2.se_co>Malanya<3.re_co>. \n"
"I am the god who watches over the\n"
"<4.se_co>horses<5.re_co> of this world. \n"
"I suppose you deserve a <6.se_co>reward<7.re_co> for\n"
"setting me free... What shall I do..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: auto_advance
#. 2: sound2
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk_00_2"
msgid "<1.au_ad><2.so><3.te_si>Shall I make you my meal?!<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (30f)
#. 3: raw
#. 4: raw
msgctxt "talk_00_3"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hahaha, I only jest...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"If a horse you love passes away from\n"
"some sort of tragic, fatal accident, it is\n"
"within my power to revive that horse...\n"
"However...<2.pa> If I detect vile intent behind\n"
"the death of your horse<3.ra>...<4.ra>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: sound2
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk_00_4"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.so>You will suffer my wrath!<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk_00_5"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I only jest...\n"
"Let me see..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
msgctxt "talk_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>...Hrm! I see you're good with horses.\n"
"All seems to be well.\n"
"\n"
"The friendship you established with\n"
"a horse really is extraordinary.\n"
"\n"
"Remember that such a friendship is\n"
"a two-way road. Horses care for you\n"
"as much as you do for them."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>...Whoa.<2.pa> Do you really not own a single\n"
"horse?\n"
"\n"
"I can't imagine going through the world\n"
"without a faithful steed to keep me\n"
"company...<3.pa> To each their own, I suppose.\n"
"In that case, I, the god of horses, can\n"
"not do much for you who avoids horses\n"
"for some reason.\n"
"If you ever do bond with a horse<4.pa> and\n"
"then tragedy strikes that proud friend,\n"
"you should come see me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_02_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>...Neigh! <2.pa>A horse, loyal and true, has\n"
"fallen during your adventures!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: sound2
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk_02_01"
msgid ""
"<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.so>I could end you, right here\n"
"and now!<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk_02_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.pa>I jest, of course...<3.pa>\n"
"Shall I bring a companion back to\n"
"travel with you once more?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_03_00"
msgid ""
"I see. <1.pa>Well, if you ever feel something\n"
"in your soul that resembles equine\n"
"heartbreak...you know where to find me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: sound2
#. 4: pause (longer)
#. 5: text_size
msgctxt "talk_03_01"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.so>To feel so...<4.pa>is unforgivable!<5.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk_03_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I jest...<2.pa> Feel free to return to me\n"
"whenever you'd like."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk_04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hrm... <2.pa>It seems like you have too many \n"
"horses registered.\n"
"\n"
"You do know you are only allowed to\n"
"own five horses in this world, right? It is\n"
"a rule that not even I can change...\n"
"Would you like to set a horse free?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "talk_05"
msgid ""
"I see. Letting go of something you love\n"
"is always so bittersweet...\n"
"Which horse would you like to set free?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk_06"
msgid ""
"Huh?<1.pa> So...you sure you don't need to\n"
"revive a horse?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: choice
msgctxt "talk_07"
msgid ""
"Hrm, you understand that you may never\n"
"get to see the horse again? You're sure?<1.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Then I shall free this horse.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"No need to worry...<2.pa> They are\n"
"strong-willed creatures and more than\n"
"capable of surviving on their own."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "talk_09"
msgid "Then let me ask you again..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "talk_09_01"
msgid "Which horse do you wish to revive?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "talk_10"
msgid "Select a loyal friend to bring back..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk_11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hrm.<2.pa> I can tell that this horse died due to\n"
"an unexpected accident. Worry not, this\n"
"happens from time to time.\n"
"The horse knows that you did not mean\n"
"for this to happen.<3.pa> Would you like for me\n"
"to revive this horse?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (long)
#. 6: pause (short)
#. 7: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_12_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So... You would like to revive this horse?\n"
"This one, specifically?\n"
"\n"
"I can do that, of course!<2.pa>\n"
"But... <3.pa>What is this...\n"
"\n"
"This horse says that YOU killed it!<4.pa> You!\n"
"<5.pa>How could you?!<6.pa> Do you plan to revive it\n"
"just to kill it again?\n"
"Are horses only a tool to you?<7.pa> Do you\n"
"treat their noble lives so casually that\n"
"you'd use them and throw them away?\n"
"If I were a horse right now..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: sound2
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: text_size
msgctxt "talk_12_01"
msgid ""
"<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.te_si><4.so><5.te_si>I'd kick you in the "
"chest!<6.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk_12_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I...<2.pa>jest.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"You accidentally struck the horse, I'm\n"
"sure. Would you like to revive this loyal,\n"
"temporarily betrayed friend?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk_13_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hrm...<2.pa> Would you like to revive\n"
"this horse?\n"
"\n"
"Oh, goodness!<3.pa> It was caught in an\n"
"explosion? Poor soul...\n"
"\n"
"Not to cast suspicion where none is\n"
"warranted, but...<4.pa>you didn't kill the horse,\n"
"did you?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: choice
msgctxt "talk_13_02"
msgid ""
"It couldn't be the case.\n"
"I'll give you the benefit of the doubt.\n"
"Would you like to revive this horse?<1.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_14_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hrm...<2.pa> You want to revive this horse?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"It seems this brave animal spent its last\n"
"moments in a fight with a Guardian.<3.pa>\n"
"It served its master well. <4.pa>I'm so moved...\n"
"Alas, if you had managed to control this\n"
"loyal beast with more skill..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: sound2
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk_14_02"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.so>I wouldn't have to revive it!<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk_14_03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I jest...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"This must have been one brave friend.\n"
"Would you like to revive it and return\n"
"it to your side?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
msgctxt "talk_15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Ah, understood!\n"
"Let me bring back this horse!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_16_01"
msgid ""
"I was successfully able to bring back \n"
"the horse!\n"
"\n"
"Next time, don't let the horse die!\n"
"Horses are your partners.<1.pa> Don't forget \n"
"that.\n"
"If you're careless with their lives, \n"
"you may regret it..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: sound2
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: text_size
msgctxt "talk_16_02"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.te_si><4.so><5.te_si>UNDERSTAND?<6.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: pause (20f)
msgctxt "talk_16_03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I jest...\n"
"<2.pa>For now!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk_17_01"
msgid ""
"Oh, you again...<1.pa>\n"
"You didn't come here to revive a\n"
"horse again, did you?\n"
"I felt I was in your debt before since you\n"
"freed me from that bud and all...but you\n"
"didn't think I'd always help out, right?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: auto_advance
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: sound2
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: text_size
msgctxt "talk_17_02"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.au_ad><3.te_si><4.so><5.te_si>I'm very busy!<6.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: single_choice
msgctxt "talk_17_03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I jest.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"I feel that there is respect in your\n"
"heart... If you can bring me something,\n"
"I would consider helping you once more.<2.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (20f)
#. 5: pause (20f)
#. 6: pause (longer)
#. 7: text_size
#. 8: set_colour (blue)
#. 9: sound2
#. 10: reset_colour
#. 11: text_size
#. 12: pause (30f)
#. 13: choice
msgctxt "talk_20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I may not look the part, but I am the <2.se_co>god\n"
"of horses<3.re_co>. I need that uh...<4.pa>that thing...\n"
"\n"
"A kind of carrot...<5.pa> One I've only eaten\n"
"once in all my many years...<6.pa>\n"
"An <7.te_si><8.se_co><9.so>endura carrot<10.re_co>!<11.te_si><12.pa>\n"
"That is what I ask of you. Fulfill this\n"
"request and I will consider helping you.<13.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk_21"
msgid ""
"I make it look easy, but it takes a lot of\n"
"energy to revive horses. Sometimes I just\n"
"need a boost before I undo<1.pa> DEATH!\n"
"So are you going to hand over an\n"
"<2.se_co>endura carrot<3.re_co>?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound2
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk_22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I see you have an <2.se_co>endura carrot<3.re_co>.\n"
"Allow me to revive your horse."
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (long)
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk_23"
msgid ""
"No you don't! <1.pa>I can tell! <2.pa>You don't even\n"
"have one <3.se_co>endura carrot<4.re_co>!\n"
"Do you take me for a fool?\n"
"Come back when you aren't a liar!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
#. 2: pause (30f)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (30f)
msgctxt "talk_24"
msgid ""
"Huh.<1.pa> Seems like you don't have a horse\n"
"in need of reviving. Well,<2.pa> that was\n"
"well-intended all the same.\n"
"If your horse ever dies, come back with\n"
"an <3.se_co>endura carrot<4.re_co>...<5.pa> Farewell."
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (short)
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "talk_25"
msgid ""
"Huh, you...<1.pa> If you would like to revive\n"
"a horse, you will need an <2.se_co>endura carrot<3.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"I assume you brought an <4.se_co>endura carrot<5.re_co>?<6.ch>"
msgstr ""

